<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-11-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-11-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="472" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d472">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">832.01/14</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dearing</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-11-05">November 5, 1930</date>.<lb/>[Received
                                November 12.]</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 222</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to report that the
                            Peruvian Junta of Government on November first accorded recognition to
                            the new Junta of Government in Brazil, even before the latter had been
                            formed.</p>
                        <p>My Brazilian colleague informs me that the Peruvian Minister in Rio de
                            Janeiro accorded recognition through the Foreign Office two days before
                            Getulio Vargas took the oath as provisional President and the
                            announcement of the composition of his Cabinet.</p>
                        <p>Respectfully yours,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Fred Morris
                            Dearing</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>